<title type="html"><![CDATA[11/22 When We Fly to Mars, Microbes Will, Too / Your Body Language Shapes Who You Are]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=98&amp;p=102#p102"><![CDATA[
Host : Zet<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Session 1 </span><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">This article is talking about microbe &amp; mars from 60 seconds science </span><br /><br /><a href="https://www.scientificamerican.com/podcast/episode/when-we-fly-to-mars-microbes-will-too/" class="postlink">https://www.scientificamerican.com/podcast/episode/when-we-fly-to-mars-microbes-will-too/</a><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Discussion</span><br />1.Have you hear about “60 seconds science” ? How do you think about this ? <br />2.Do you have any good tips to deal with bathroom humid problem? Or got some special experience about that. Please share with us. <br />3.If mars were a good place for human living, would you like to be there? What kinds of factor will force you to live there rather than living in earth? <br />4.Do you think mars should be more clean for human living or should be more nature and verity microorganisms like earth? <br />5.If you can hatch certain kind of microorganisms to separate in mars, what kind of microbe you will hatch?<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold"><br />Session 2 </span><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">The speaker mentions that body language affects how others see us, but it may also change how we see ourselves </span><br /><br /><a href="https://www.ted.com/talks/amy_cuddy_your_body_language_shapes_who_you_are" class="postlink">https://www.ted.com/talks/amy_cuddy_your_body_language_shapes_who_you_are</a><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Discussion</span><br />1.Do you think body language is really affecting yourself when you do it? We did some of them when we grow up. Share your experience for us. <br />2.Do you think that you deceive yourself to be something is really helping you to achieve your goal? Did you try that before? <br />3.Do you have some great body language which can share with us? Or some bad experience can share? <br />4.Do you think Tai Chi (太極) or some Chinese kungfu are the same theory as this rule? Let psychical to influence physical? <br />5.If the speaker’s speech is worked on you. Do you think you can shape other people to force them to do something you want them to do?<br /><br />Agenda<br />7:00-7:25 Greetings and free talk<br />7:25-7:30 Opening remarks/ Newcomers self-introduction/ Grouping<br />(Session I)<br />7:30 ~ 8:05pm discussion session (35 mins)<br />8:05 ~ 8:20pm summarization (15 mins)<br />8:20 ~ 8:25pm Regrouping <br />(Session II)<br />8:25 ~ 8:35pm Taking a 10 minutes break (Intermission)<br />8:35 ~ 9:10pm discussion session (35 mins)<br />9:10 ~9:25pm summarization (15 mins)<br />9:25 ~ 9:30pm Concluding remarks/feedback from newcomers<br /><br />The meeting place of Thursday:<br />摩斯漢堡明曜店 (明曜百貨後面第二條巷子地下室)<br />台北市大安區仁愛路四段151巷37號B1樓<br />捷運資訊： 近台北捷運 - 板南線 - 忠孝敦化站 (步行約5分鐘)<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500.帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=49">josh</a> — Wed Nov 22, 2017 1:40 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
